<section class="faq--root">
  <div class="faq--header">
    <h2 class="faq--title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="faq--subtitle">Everything you need to know before your first bag.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq--card-wrapper">
    <div class="faq--card">

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does "hulless" actually mean?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>Every popcorn kernel has a hull — it's the outer shell that lets pressure build until the kernel pops. With hulless varieties like ours, that hull is so thin it shatters into near-invisible fragments when popped. The result? No tough bits stuck in your teeth or scratching your gums.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How should I pop these kernels?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>Stovetop, air popper, or microwave popper bowl — any method works great. We recommend stovetop with a tablespoon of your favorite oil and medium-high heat. Give the pot a shake every few seconds once popping starts. Our kernels pop up smaller and more tender than standard popcorn, so keep the heat consistent and don't wait too long between pops.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is your popcorn safe for people with braces or dental work?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>Many of our customers specifically seek us out because they have braces, veneers, implants, or other dental work. While we always recommend checking with your dentist, our hulless kernels produce significantly fewer hard hull fragments than conventional popcorn — which is the main reason dentists tell patients to avoid it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How long do the kernels stay fresh?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>Stored in a cool, dry place with the bag sealed, our kernels stay fresh for up to two years. Once opened, we recommend using them within six months for the best pop and flavor. There's no need to refrigerate — just keep the bag tightly closed between uses.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is this popcorn non-GMO and allergen-friendly?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>Yes. Our popcorn is a single-ingredient product — 100% popcorn kernels, nothing else. There are no GMOs, no additives, and no preservatives. It's naturally gluten-free, nut-free, soy-free, and dairy-free. It's processed on our family farm with no shared equipment for common allergens.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq--item">
        <button class="faq--question" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What's your shipping and return policy?</span>
          <svg class="faq--icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq--answer">
          <div class="faq--answer-inner">
            <p>We ship within 1–2 business days via USPS from our farm in Indiana. Most orders arrive in 3–5 business days. If you're not happy with your popcorn for any reason, reach out to us and we'll make it right — whether that's a replacement or a refund. We stand behind every bag.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* ── Theme reset ── */
  .faq--root,
  .faq--root *,
  .faq--root *::before,
  .faq--root *::after {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif !important;
    margin: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .faq--root h2 {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif !important;
    font-style: normal !important;
    text-transform: none !important;
  }

  .faq--root button {
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif !important;
  }

  /* ── Section root ── */
  .faq--root {
    padding: 50px 100px 70px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .faq--header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .faq--title {
    font-weight: 700 !important;
    font-size: 28px !important;
    line-height: 32px !important;
    color: #000;
    margin: 0 0 20px !important;
  }

  .faq--subtitle {
    font-weight: 400 !important;
    font-size: 16px !important;
    color: #000;
    margin: 0 !important;
  }

  /* ── Card wrapper ── */
  .faq--card-wrapper {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq--card {
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.09);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* ── FAQ item ── */
  .faq--item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #edebe8;
  }

  .faq--item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* ── Question button ── */
  .faq--question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 18px 24px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 500 !important;
    font-size: 15px !important;
    line-height: 22px !important;
    color: #222;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq--question:hover {
    background: #fafaf8;
  }

  /* ── Icon ── */
  .faq--icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    color: #007494;
  }

  .faq--item.is-open .faq--icon line:first-child {
    opacity: 0;
  }

  .faq--item.is-open .faq--icon {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  /* ── Answer ── */
  .faq--answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.35s ease;
  }

  .faq--answer-inner {
    padding: 0 24px 18px;
  }

  .faq--answer-inner p {
    font-weight: 400 !important;
    font-size: 14px !important;
    line-height: 22px !important;
    color: #555;
    margin: 0 !important;
  }

  /* ── Mobile ── */
  @media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {
    .faq--root {
      padding: 40px 16px 50px;
    }

    .faq--title {
      font-size: 22px !important;
      line-height: 28px !important;
    }

    .faq--subtitle {
      font-size: 14px !important;
    }

    .faq--question {
      padding: 16px 18px;
      font-size: 14px !important;
      line-height: 20px !important;
    }

    .faq--answer-inner {
      padding: 0 18px 16px;
    }

    .faq--answer-inner p {
      font-size: 13px !important;
      line-height: 20px !important;
    }
  }

  /* ── Tablet ── */
  @media only screen and (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1023px) {
    .faq--root {
      padding: 50px 40px 60px;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
(function() {
  var items = document.querySelectorAll('.faq--item');
  if (!items.length) return;

  items.forEach(function(item) {
    var btn = item.querySelector('.faq--question');
    var answer = item.querySelector('.faq--answer');
    if (!btn || !answer) return;

    btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
      var isOpen = item.classList.contains('is-open');

      // Close all items (accordion behavior)
      items.forEach(function(other) {
        var otherAnswer = other.querySelector('.faq--answer');
        var otherBtn = other.querySelector('.faq--question');
        other.classList.remove('is-open');
        if (otherAnswer) otherAnswer.style.maxHeight = null;
        if (otherBtn) otherBtn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });

      // Toggle clicked item
      if (!isOpen) {
        item.classList.add('is-open');
        answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
      }
    });
  });
})();
</script>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "FAQ",
  "class": "section--faq",
  "presets": [{
    "name": "FAQ",
    "category": "Text"
  }]
}
{% endschema %}
